The Herald Farirai Machivenyika Senior Reporter
President Mnangagwa has today launched the Agricultural Finance Company Holdings, formerly Agribank. The AFC Holdings has four subsidiaries: AFC Commercial Bank, AFC Insurance, AFC Land and Development Bank, and AFC Leasing Company. <img class="wp-image-544920 size-large" src="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/04/Untitled-2-11-680x453.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="453" srcset="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/04/Untitled-2-11.jpg 680w, https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/04/Untitled-2-11-360x240.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> President Mnangagwa leaves Hurudza House accompanied by Lands, Agriculture, Fisheries, Water and Rural Resettlement Minister Anxious Masuka. Pictures by Tawanda Mudimu The new institution will provide funding across the whole agriculture value chain from communal to large-scale farmers. In his remarks, the President said the institution was key to the recovery of the agriculture sector.